Microbes with resistance to arsenic increases the possibility of new types of life on Earth, or elsewhere
Discovery of strange bacteria, which can use arsenic as one of its nutrients, extends the area to search for new forms of life on Earth, and perhaps even further.
Researchers discovered unusual bacteria here in the country and say that it is a sign that life has opportunities, which stands outside the main elements that were still considered to be the basic.
"This organization has double capacity."
"may either because of phosphorus or arsenic." Growth
"This is a very special, but it is not proof that it is a form of really 'an alien' life," on this fact Paul C. W. Davies of the Arizona State University, spoluautor report, which appeared in a Thursday in the online edition of the journal Science.
Long was considered necessary for the life of six main elements - carbon, hydrogen and nitrogen, oxygen, phosphorus and sulphur.
However, scientists have found that the bacteria, discovered in Mono Lake in California, are able to continue in growth after the arsenic will replace phosphorus.
"Will you wonder what everything is still possible," said Ariel D. Anbar of Arizona State University, spoluautor report.
This finding is important for searching for life outside the country, as researchers must be able to identify life and to know how life may look, Anbar said.
Study focuses on the microbes found in the country.
However, the report about this news published, to discussion, betrayed that details about her award, caused widespread speculation on the Internet, that the report reveals the discovery of extraterrestrial life.
This is not the case.
Discovery "shows that other planetary organisms may be able to use other elements that drive biochemistry and that set of elements, which we consider 'standard', may not be so absolutely necessary for life," said Charles cockell, Professor at the planetary and space science research institute, Milton Keynes, Open University, in Great Britain.
Cockell was not part of the research team.
"This work is unusual because it shows the replacement of one element of the other element in basic biochemistry and biochemical structure," he added cockell.
This was not a random prize.
Felisa wolfe-simon of astrobiologického Institute in NASA, which the study led, has focused on the Mono Lake, since it has high levels of arsenic.
Arsenic and phosphorus are chemically very similar to the elements, she thought so that the microbe is exposed to the elements, may be able to replace the one for the other.
"poisonous arsenic is mainly because its chemical behavior is very similar phosphorus."
"The result is that the organisms can very hard to these elements from each other."
"However, arsenic is so different, that as well as phosphorus is not working. If they get to the organism, to begin work Anbar biochemical processes," he explained.
Scientists gather the bacteria known as gfaj-1 and display is increasing the concentration of arsenic bacteria, which are able to adapt and growth.
Microbes are better at of phosphorus, but also due to the fact that they can survive with a arzenem, increases the possibility that the form of life, which uses arsenic, it can occur naturally, and either elsewhere in the country or to another planet or a month, where the arsenic is more common.
Jamie S. Foster, Assistant Professor Microbiology at the University of Florida, said that the idea of arsenic, which could be replaced by phosphorus, is not new, but never found an example, on which would prove this fact.
Arsenic was more common in the old days in the country, she said, and so the scientists have speculated that it could use the previous forms of life.
"It suggests that there may be other ways to create life, not only in the way the created in the early period of the country," said Foster, who was not part of the research team wolfe-simona.
Research has been supported by NASA, the Department of Energy and the National Institute of Health
