Red Bull triumphs in Formula One with the secret weapons from a company Siemens
Software proposes improvement in vehicles in real time.
From the time when the Red Bull vpadnul Formula 1 in 2004, to show his history in this exceptional world speed is characterized by surprise and success.
At first, but no one took too seriously the newcomer's options for this team, and also through an upward trend in recent times, all bets were on the triumph of Ferrari Fernando alonsa.
Without wishing to reduce riding the ability of champion, the Germans sebastiana vettela, or the possibility of Renault, which drives his car engine, legend - born 'secret weapon "in the world of Formula 1, which multinational Siemens put it in the hands of the Red bullu that made him so the winning team.
This is, in fact, the Executive software to simulate Marches, which the German company said on the market in 2007 for the very distant car sport.
The plm, this powerful software machine had been used to design assembly lines in manufacturing plants around the world, in energy plants and for the apparatus with high accuracy.
His goal is to faithfully to reproduce the product or replicated real created the process before it is, so as to avoid the unnecessary errors and spending.
Plm facilitate development of camera canon, aircraft sukhoi or of noted of commercial vehicles of the Nissan brand.
Siegfried russwurm, director of the industrial division of the company Siemens, explains that the use of this software apparatus has allowed the team Red Bull place "in the next few hours, in almost real time" modifications and improvements, which otherwise detect during races and tests.
Russwurm says that in 1992, the stables on average 10 technicians who were able to make a maximum of three or four improvement in one period.
In the team Red Bull works today to 180 young highly qualified professionals with an information technology, who analyzed and propose every kind of modification racing vehicles.
The head of Siemens, explained that the software plm is able to analyze and improve all elements of the vehicles Red Bull racing with the exception of the engine, which fully in charge Renault.
Modifikují materials, fuel, aerodynamika and security elements.
Change is possible transfer of the virtual reality to the fact in less than 24 hours thanks to advanced production systems using a laser and highly technologically advanced autokláv.
The only limit this technical achievements is the amount of $40 million, representing the maximum, which each team Formula 1 may issue for each period to improve their competitiveness.
Red Bull set up about 50 km from the London race top technology used to design and manufacture of their race cars.
This is about the two buildings, in which is limited access to audit - especially in the journalists.
All what is going on here, it is considered as a "great secret."
The list of interested this project of 580 people, including two pilots - Champion vettela and Mark webbera.
The hero of the Red bullu is in Formula 1, without a doubt fresh champion Sebastian vettel.
For the nezměrnými technological means that mark energy drinks inserted into his participation in racing headings, however, have other protagonists, whose aid is invaluable, and there is no one knows.
Head of production technology, Steve nevey claims that five years ago, it was possible to say that progress in the research and development of the vehicles contributed to the victory of 50%, and the rest was due to drivers.
At present, the ratio has changed and the technology behind the achievements of the 85%, while pilots contribute from 15%.
Nevey recognises that vettel or webber will never be replaced by computer technology, as they are "the unpredictable gladiators."
