The United States changing rules for giving visas
People will have to resort to the center of services for visa applicants, before the pohovorem to consular department; the costs will be lower and will shorten the waiting period.
From 10 January 2011 will change the process of considering a visa to the United States embassy and consulates.
With the new procedure, most of the applicants will have to turn to the center of services for visa applicants, basically from English asc before the pohovorem to consular department.
Staff of the asc removes the biometric information applicants, and you will be before pohovorem evaluated the Consular Department.
The new procedure will have some advantages, among which is the following:
Total cost of completing the visas will be lower, will no longer pay the fee for agreeing to the meeting, the second for processing applications and another for the delivery of the document of the transport service.
The applicant will only one fee, which will cover all the three services.
The current tariff will remain unchanged: a sum equal to 140 dollars for a tourist visa, $150 for cases of visa applications, including visa for temporary staff and 390 dollars for a visa for traders and investors.
People who want to restore their visa, will not have to undergo an interview with consular official, but only to turn to the nearest asc, where will submit their documents and they will be taken fingerprints.
Due to the fact that the biometric information will be taken in asc applicants, who will require a second meeting with conversation at the consular department, here they spend less time than in the past.
As well, those who will apply for a visa to consulates in Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay extra fee for the service, $26.
For more information about the new procedure to apply for visas, visit the Web page http:// mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201 _ visas-faqs.html
