World plan to restore lighting
The UN yesterday proposed in Cancun plan for the reconstruction of domestic lighting, lighting, business and industrial area in 100 countries with a view to reducing greenhouse effect, ges, which equates to almost one third of further restrictions on the climate, which is to be achieved for the stabilisation of the planet from now to 2020.
This ambitious plan is in a stage of large concrete projects, which the UN wants to push through in Cancun, to kompenzovala the absence of difficult to viable commitments to reduce on the industrialised countries.
According to the plan submitted yesterday, if red light bulbs, which still monopolizují 50 to 70% of the market, will replace bulbs fluokompaktními or, better yet, bulbs with elektroluminiscentními diodes, del or "ice" in English, the big quantity of 1.8 billion tonnes, gt, ges on the planet incurred due to the lighting would odbouralo emissions.
Lighting is responsible for 8% of the world's emissions.
Is it the equivalent of 70% of the emissions from car park on the planet.
In Copenhagen last year, the big countries with significant on issues such as the United States, Canada, China, Europe and others, between them involved in the voluntary plans to reduce the, which should allow the reduction of global ges of 53 gt on 49 GT.
But will be deducted from the record of five more GT, to be achieved by the year 2020 stabilizing climate warming to 2 degrees Celsius to be excluded, that doesn't get out of control.
In luminous sheets bulbs 95% of the energy to disperse in the form of heat and the rest, including. 5%, is a product of light.
With fluokompaktními bulbs energy consumption reduces about 75%, and with new bulbs with del zredukujeme this consumption twice more.
Fluokompaktní light bulbs can stand on average from 6,000 to 10,000 hours.
New light bulbs with del, such, which said this week in the production Philips - this company was allegedly involved in the study of the UN - have a life expectancy of 25,000 hours and consumes about 80% less energy than hot lamp, which gives us an idea about the possible savings with the compensation plan, which would be applied in 100 countries.
All these new light bulbs can also work with reostaty and emit less heat.
And contain no mercury.
A number of experts expressed reservations about the fluokompaktním light bulbs, because they contain mercury and is to be separate as dangerous waste, which still is not possible in the developing countries, unless producers would set up sběrny.
But, as the report notes, the main source of mercury emissions is not fluokompaktní light bulb, but rather on the planet Mercury thermal coal power plants that emit many needed for the production of electricity promrhané in luminous sheets bulbs.
Only in the United States these center put into circulation of 25,000 tons of mercury per year.
Report also detail says profits, which would be from this international programme of each country.
For example, Indonesia would thus save billion dollars a year for the purchase of electricity and eight million tonnes of CO2, which is the equivalent of 3.5 thermal power stations, whose construction would have cost 2.5 billion
