South Korea's government will adopt a law, called "peciválský," which prohibit adolescentům play online games, after midnight, that block access to them, responsible government officials said.
The draft law will be submitted to Parliament in December, so that he can ask companies operating online games for blocking access to these Games after midnight to anyone under 16 years old, said leaders of the Ministry of Culture and the Ministry for the family.
"Many of the children with learning plays these Games all night and then have problems in school and are not able to lead a normal life during the day."
"We do not believe that this law is necessary for it, so that it could be ensured their health and their right to sleep," he said to AFP Yeah Rin, senior official at the Ministry, which is in charge of the bill.
Online games will be newly accessible from 6 hours in the morning.
Companies will have one year to it, to prepare for the application of the law, he said.
The Government also assumes that asking the company to reduce daily time access to these games for the young, whose parents on this request, said owner.
